2. Page Descriptions
Homepage (index.html)

This page will introduce my website, which is basically a collection of resources that helped me throughout this course. It will give a short explanation of each topic and help users navigate to the different pages. The goal is to make it easy to find useful information all in one place.

Using the Code Editor (code-editor.html)

This page will talk about the code editor I used and how it helped me during the course. I’ll include tips and examples that made coding easier, like organizing files and writing cleaner code.

HTML – Semantic Elements (semantic-html.html)

This page will focus on resources that helped me understand semantic HTML. I’ll explain things like header, section, and article tags, and how they make websites more organized and easier to read.

CSS – Layout and Responsive Design (css-layout.html)

This page will include resources that helped me learn CSS. I’ll explain layout techniques and how to make a website responsive so it works on different screen sizes like phones and laptops.

Accessibility (accessibility.html)

This page will go over resources about making websites accessible. I’ll include things like alt text, readable fonts, and good color contrast so everyone can use the website.

Ethical Issues in Web Development (ethics.html)

This page will talk about ethics in web development. I’ll include resources about being honest with content, protecting user privacy, and using information responsibly.

Validation for HTML and CSS Code (validation.html)

This page will explain how I checked my code using validators. I’ll include examples of fixing errors and why validation is important for making a site work correctly.

Using Generative Artificial Intelligence (ai.html)

This page will explain how AI tools helped me during the course. I’ll also talk about why it’s important to double-check AI-generated content instead of just trusting it.

